1 moves to amend the bill on page 14, lines 5-6, by inserting the following between the lines:
2
3 "SECTION 6.5.(a) G.S. 15-187 reads as rewritten:
4 "§ 15-187. Death by administration of lethal drugs.penalty.
5 Death by electrocution under sentence of law and death by the administration of lethal gas
6 under sentence of law are abolished. Any person convicted of a criminal offense and sentenced
7 to death shall be executed in accordance with G.S. 15-188 and the remainder of this Article. The
8 default method of executing a death sentence shall be as described in G.S. 15-188(a). However,
9 if the method adopted in G.S. 15-188(a) is declared unconstitutional by a North Carolina court
10 of competent jurisdiction then the provisions in G.S. 15-188(b) shall apply. The warden of
11 Central Prison may obtain and employ the drugs and equipment necessary to carry out the
12 provisions of this Article, regardless of contrary provisions in Chapter 90 of the General
13 Statutes.Statutes; however, if the method of executing a death under G.S. 15-188(a) is
14 unavailable for any other reason, then the provisions in G.S. 15-188(b) shall apply."
15 SECTION 6.5.(b) G.S. 15-188 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 15-188. Manner and place of execution.
17 (a) In accordance with G.S. 15-187,Unless subsection (b) of this section applies, the
18 mode of executing a death sentence must in every case be by administering to the convict or felon
19 an intravenous injection of a substance or substances in a lethal quantity sufficient to cause death
20 and until the person is dead, and that procedure shall be determined by the Secretary of the
21 Department of Adult Correction, who shall ensure compliance with the federal and State
22 constitutions; and when any person, convict or felon shall be sentenced by any court of the State
23 having competent jurisdiction to be so executed, the punishment shall only be inflicted within a
24 permanent death chamber which the superintendent of the State penitentiary is hereby authorized
25 and directed to provide within the walls of the North Carolina penitentiary at Raleigh, North
26 Carolina. The superintendent of the State penitentiary shall also cause to be provided, in
27 conformity with this Article, the necessary appliances for the infliction of the punishment of
28 death and qualified personnel to set up and prepare the injection, administer the preinjections,
29 insert the IV catheter, and to perform other tasks required for this procedure in accordance with
30 the requirements of this Article.
31 (b) The Secretary of the Department of Adult Correction, within 120 days of notice of a
32 judgment being entered that the method in subsection (a) of this section has been declared
